race.description: Melbourne Cup Day In Mildura Mdn Plate
race.comment: MISSION GOLD (3) is the one with upside that appeals here off an encouraging return at Mt Gambier, running on well from back in the field to grab fourth. That was his first run for the Payne yard having shown ability in better maidens in NSW last time in. Better placed out to 1000m here and can get the job done. MORAL TURPITUDE (4) resumes. The debut effort at Seymour last time in reads quite well for this behind some talented types before some sound efforts afterwards. The draw isn't ideal but he can roll forward and run a bold race. BOLSHOI BABE (11) debuted over 1100m at Bordertown and ran well for third. That was a fairly low maiden but she's open to improvement and can figure. JURA VAUDOIS (6) resumes. Her form was mixed last time in but the best efforts have her firmly in the mix. CHEERS TO US (5) is off a long break, watch the betting.
